1️⃣ Get started with Express:
is a web application framework for Node.js.
It is designed for building web applications and APIs.
Express.js basically helps you manage everything, from routes, to handling requests and views.

2️⃣ Install Postman:
Postman is a Google Chrome app for interacting with HTTP APIs. It presents you with a friendly GUI for constructing requests and reading responses.

3️⃣ Working with the requests CRUD
Create   :  POST
Read     :  GET
Update   :  PATCH
            PUT
Delete   :  DELETE

4️⃣ Get started with the Routes:
A Router instance is a complete middleware and routing system, it is often referred to as a “mini-app”. 

5️⃣ Create the Middleware:
Middleware functions are functions that have access to the request object ( req ), the response object ( res ), and the next function in the application's request-response cycle.

6️⃣ Files Structures
Controllers
   tourController.js
   userController.js
Routers
   tourRouters.js
   userRouters.js
app.js
server.js

7️⃣ Setting up ESLint:
ESLint is a static code analysis tool for identifying problematic patterns found in JavaScript code.
Install all the package that ESLint need to work:
npm i eslint prettier eslint-config-prettier eslint-plugin-prettier eslint-config-airbnb eslint-plugin-node eslint-plugin-import eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y eslint-plugin-react --save-dev